===Usage===
This template rounds {{{1}}} to {{{2}}} decimal places (goes the other way for negatives) and includes trailing zeros.  Scientific notation is used for numbers greater than or equal to 1{{e|9}}, or less than 1{{e|âˆ’4}}.

Compare:
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|2.0004|3}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|2.0004|3}}
**whereas <tt><nowiki>{{#expr:2.0004 round 3}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{#expr:2.0004 round 3}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|0.000020004|7}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|0.000020004|7}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|0|8}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|0|8}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|154268|-3}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|154268|-3}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|1200004|-1}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|1200004|-1}}
**whereas <tt><nowiki>{{#expr:1200004round-1}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{#expr:1200004round-1}}, even though <tt><nowiki>{{#expr:1300004round-1}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{#expr:1300004round-1}} (see [[m:Help:Format produced by expr]]) 
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|1300004|-1}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|1300004|-1}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|4.1e6|9}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|4.1e6|9}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|4.1e6|10}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|4.1e6|10}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|1542689271|-7}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|1542689271|-7}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|1542689271|2}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|1542689271|2}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|7e9|-9}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|7e9|-9}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|-123|1}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|-123|1}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|-1200007|-2}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|-1200007|-2}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|-1234567899|-7}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|-1234567899|-7}}

As with #expr, the total number of significant digits is not more than 14:
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|1234567890.123456789|10}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|1234567890.123456789|10}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|123456789.0123456789|10}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|123456789.0123456789|10}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|.0001234567890123456789|20}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd|.0001234567890123456789|20}}

===Internal details===
The template uses three subtemplates:
*{{tl|rnd/-}} â€” for trailing zeros
*{{tl|rnd/e+}} â€” for scientific notation for numbers greater than or equal to 10<sup>9</sup> or less than or equal to âˆ’10<sup>9</sup>
*{{tl|rnd/eâˆ’}} â€” for scientific notation for numbers greater than âˆ’10<sup>âˆ’4</sup> and less than 10<sup>âˆ’4</sup> but not equal to zero
