[[Category:Mathematical function templates|{{PAGENAME}}]]
</includeonly>

{{Documentation subpage}} This subtemplate of {{tl|rnd}} adds trailing zeros. It takes two parameters. #the number to be displayed #the number of significant figures to be displayed after the decimal point
*<tt><nowiki>{{rnd/-|2|3}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd/-|2|3}} *<tt><nowiki>{{rnd/-|1E+5|3}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{rnd/-|1E+5|3}}
It's used by {{tl|rnd}}. *"<tt><nowiki>{{#expr:2.0004 round 3}}</nowiki></tt>" gives "{{#expr:2.0004 round 3}}" *"<tt><nowiki>{{rnd|2.0004|3}}</nowiki></tt>" gives "{{rnd|2.0004|3}}" <includeonly> [[Category:Template subpages|{{PAGENAME}}]] </includeonly>

{{Documentation subpage}}

===Usage===
This template calculates the (decimal) [[w:order of magnitude|order of magnitude]] of numbers within the ranges 10<sup>300</sup> to 10<sup>âˆ’300</sup> and âˆ’10<sup>âˆ’300</sup> to âˆ’10<sup>300</sup>.

The acceptable input and the output produced are optimized for use in other templates. 
*The hyphen (not a true minus sign) is used for negative numbers.
*No separator is used for thousands. 
*The template gives 0 for 0.  Although, strictly speaking, this is mathematically incorrect it has been designed this way so as to be more useful in other templates.  An important example of this is that when used by {{tl|convert}} 0&nbsp;Â°C or 0&nbsp;Â°F is considered to be on the same order of magnitude as Â±1&nbsp;Â°C or Â±1&nbsp;Â°F respectively.

===Examples===
*<tt><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|123400}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{Order of magnitude|123400}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|12340}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{Order of magnitude|12340}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|1234}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{Order of magnitude|1234}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|123.4}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{Order of magnitude|123.4}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|12.34}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{Order of magnitude|12.34}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|1.234}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{Order of magnitude|1.234}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|.1234}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{Order of magnitude|.1234}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|.01234}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{Order of magnitude|.01234}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|0}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{Order of magnitude|0}}
*<tt><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude}}</nowiki></tt> â†’ {{Order of magnitude}}

===Incorrect usage===
The input must be an unformatted number, or the template will emit errors:
*<code><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|}}</nowiki></code> â†’ <strong class="error">Expression error: Unexpected = operator</strong>
*<code><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|123,400}}</nowiki></code> â†’ <strong class="error">Expression error: Unrecognised punctuation character ","</strong>
*<code><nowiki>{{Order of magnitude|foo}}</nowiki></code> â†’ <strong class="error">Expression error: Unrecognised word "foo"</strong>
